Nicholas Figueroa, 23, died in a gas explosion on New York City's Second Avenue on March 26 .
He was paying the bill on a blind date at a sushi restaurant when three buildings in New York's East Village were destroyed .
A plumber allegedly admitted to creating an illegal gas connection in the building, allegedly at the request of the landlord .
The family, who are afraid for their safety, say it still 'wants justice' and those responsible for the explosion to be punished .